WEBVTT

00:01.935 --> 00:05.004
♪ It seems today
that all you see ♪

00:05.006 --> 00:08.140
♪ Is violence in movies
and sex on TV ♪

00:08.142 --> 00:11.844
♪ But where are those
good old-fashioned values ♪

00:11.846 --> 00:14.847
♪ On which we used to rely?

00:14.849 --> 00:18.283
♪ Lucky there's a family guy

00:18.285 --> 00:21.620
♪ Lucky there's a man
who positively can do ♪

00:21.622 --> 00:23.122
♪ All the things that make us

00:23.124 --> 00:24.857
♪ Laugh and cry

00:24.859 --> 00:30.062
♪ He's... a...
Fam... ily... Guy! ♪

00:34.968 --> 00:36.301
Peter, come on,
get dressed.

00:36.303 --> 00:37.669
We're late
for church.

00:37.671 --> 00:39.204
I don't want to
go to church.

00:39.206 --> 00:41.974
I always feel like that
priest has it in for me.

00:41.976 --> 00:43.976
Body of Christ.

00:43.978 --> 00:45.978
Body of Christ.

00:45.980 --> 00:47.012
Butt of Christ.

00:47.014 --> 00:49.381
Aah! Lois,
trade me.
No.

00:50.483 --> 00:52.684
You're not wearing that
to church, are you?

00:52.686 --> 00:53.886
What? Yeah. Why not?

00:53.888 --> 00:55.554
This is what
I always wear.

00:55.556 --> 00:56.855
She's right, man.

00:56.857 --> 00:58.057
It's Sunday. Get noticed.

00:58.059 --> 01:00.125
I'll be in the car.

01:01.361 --> 01:04.063
I'm getting tired of you wearing
the same thing every day.

01:04.065 --> 01:05.864
Look, that shirt's got
a hole in it.

01:05.866 --> 01:08.700
I'd like to point out that Jesus
wore the same thing every day.

01:08.702 --> 01:11.070
And you didn't hear Alice
giving him a hard time about it.

01:11.072 --> 01:12.504
Who?
Wasn't that her name?

01:12.506 --> 01:13.705
Let's just get to church.

01:13.707 --> 01:15.074
And afterward,
you're going to the mall

01:15.076 --> 01:16.341
to go clothes shopping.

01:16.343 --> 01:17.843
Well, you're
coming with me.

01:17.845 --> 01:20.179
Last time I tried shopping
without you, it was a disaster.

01:20.181 --> 01:21.580
Hey, I'm home.

01:21.582 --> 01:23.549
I got groceries.
You what?

01:23.551 --> 01:24.883
Yeah, I was driving past there,

01:24.885 --> 01:26.718
and we were out
of some stuff, so I...

01:26.720 --> 01:28.921
You listen to me,
you son of a bitch!

01:28.923 --> 01:30.889
I've got one thing
in this lifetime!

01:30.891 --> 01:32.691
One thing.
(groaning)

01:32.693 --> 01:35.694
You always say I never
do anything around here.

01:35.696 --> 01:39.064
Yeah, I like saying that more
than I like you doing things.

01:39.066 --> 01:41.100
Dad, I got the rest
from the car. Where...?

01:41.102 --> 01:42.601
Chris, run!
You were right!

01:42.603 --> 01:43.869
She didn't appreciate it!

01:43.871 --> 01:46.071
Oh, crap!

01:46.073 --> 01:47.706
CHRIS:
Ow!

01:47.708 --> 01:48.874
That's right.

01:48.876 --> 01:50.776
I do groceries.

01:55.381 --> 01:57.282
All right, even though
we just walked in,

01:57.284 --> 02:00.219
and this whole place is one
hallway, let's consult the map.

02:00.221 --> 02:01.887
Okay.

02:01.889 --> 02:03.222
Uh-oh.

02:03.224 --> 02:05.491
(gunshot)

02:08.094 --> 02:11.063
I'll bet we can find you
some new clothes in here.

02:11.065 --> 02:13.899
PETER:
Hey, Lois, are you sure
this place is for men?

02:13.901 --> 02:15.134
Yes, Peter, it's for everyone.

02:15.136 --> 02:17.569
Really? 'Cause this-this
kind of looks like a dress.

02:17.571 --> 02:19.805
Peter, it's fine.
Come on out.

02:20.740 --> 02:22.875
Ha! You gaybo!

02:25.278 --> 02:26.612
Hang on, Peter.

02:26.614 --> 02:28.914
I'm gonna go look for a couple
things for me in here.

02:28.916 --> 02:30.115
I'll be right back.

02:30.117 --> 02:31.617
Okay, Lois, I'll
be right here,

02:31.619 --> 02:34.153
standing uncomfortably close to
the unnecessary piano player

02:34.155 --> 02:35.921
in the middle of the mall.

02:35.923 --> 02:37.789
♪

02:37.791 --> 02:39.958
So, what's it like
now that you've made it?

02:39.960 --> 02:41.260
Did you ever have
a bank account

02:41.262 --> 02:42.928
full of pedestrians'
disinterested smiles?

02:42.930 --> 02:44.463
You're amazing.

02:44.465 --> 02:46.999
I'm gonna sit Indian-style
on top of your piano.

02:48.301 --> 02:51.103
There aren't enough verses
in any song I could write

02:51.105 --> 02:53.939
that would express how much
hatred I have in my heart.

02:53.941 --> 02:56.208
You talk like a book.

02:57.944 --> 02:59.111
Hey, Lois,
how about we try Sears?

02:59.113 --> 03:00.312
They got good stuff.

03:00.314 --> 03:02.114
Peter, nobody's been
in Sears for decades.

03:02.116 --> 03:03.782
Oh, come on.
When I was a boy,

03:03.784 --> 03:05.617
we always used to go
clothes shopping at Sears.

03:05.619 --> 03:07.219
Trust me. They'll have
everything I need.

03:12.792 --> 03:13.959
What the hell happened here?

03:13.961 --> 03:15.394
Look out!

03:17.630 --> 03:19.698
(muffled speaking)

03:19.700 --> 03:21.800
He wants to know
who you are.

03:21.802 --> 03:24.136
We seek clothes
for the cold times.

03:24.138 --> 03:26.138
(muffled speaking)

03:26.140 --> 03:29.041
He says he'll take you to
the clothes for herbs and meat.

03:29.043 --> 03:30.676
Well, we can probably come up

03:30.678 --> 03:32.644
with some herbs
and meat, right, Peter?

03:32.646 --> 03:33.879
Peter?

03:33.881 --> 03:35.480
I'm with them now.

03:35.482 --> 03:36.982
No girls allowed.

03:36.984 --> 03:39.284
(tires squealing)

03:43.323 --> 03:45.324
See, Lois, now,
this is more like it.

03:45.326 --> 03:47.326
What the hell?
Why won't this button?

03:47.328 --> 03:48.994
It's the same size
I always get.

03:48.996 --> 03:51.163
Maybe you put on a
few pounds, sweetie.

03:51.165 --> 03:53.065
Lois, I weigh the same
293 pounds today

03:53.067 --> 03:54.499
that I weighed
in grade school.

03:54.501 --> 03:57.035
Perhaps it's this lump
on the side of your neck, sir.

03:57.037 --> 03:58.670
Oh, my God, Peter!

03:58.672 --> 04:00.372
How long have you
had that thing?

04:00.374 --> 04:01.673
I-I don't know.

04:01.675 --> 04:03.842
We got to go see
Dr. Hartman right away.

04:03.844 --> 04:05.677
Oh, my God, what if
it's something serious?

04:05.679 --> 04:06.878
It's all right,
it's all right.

04:06.880 --> 04:09.014
We'll be in good hands
with Dr. Hartman.

04:09.016 --> 04:11.016
He handled
my reassignment surgery.

04:11.018 --> 04:14.219
I think, emotionally, I've
always been a lizard, you know?

04:14.221 --> 04:15.854
And now, I feel
comfortable finally

04:15.856 --> 04:17.189
in my leathery,
scaly skin.

04:17.191 --> 04:18.757
Kids, if you need me,

04:18.759 --> 04:21.627
I'll be on the wall making
rapid, darting glances.

04:23.863 --> 04:26.198
Is this just to get out
of my parents' visit?

04:26.200 --> 04:27.366
No.

04:27.368 --> 04:28.567
(doorbell rings)

04:28.569 --> 04:30.636
BABS:
Hello!

04:34.073 --> 04:35.874
No,    <i>you'</i>stupid!

04:35.876 --> 04:37.409
Oh, hello, Griffins.

04:37.411 --> 04:39.044
What can I help
you with today?

04:39.046 --> 04:42.547
Dr. Hartman, Peter has a huge
lump growing on his neck.

04:42.549 --> 04:44.049
Mrs. Griffin,
that's called a "head."

04:44.051 --> 04:45.584
I've been fooled
by that one before.

04:45.586 --> 04:47.286
Well, will you
take a look at it?

04:47.288 --> 04:48.920
I think it might
be a tumor.

04:48.922 --> 04:50.289
Okay, let's
have a look.

04:51.224 --> 04:53.892
Oh, yes, it appears
that there is a...

04:53.894 --> 04:55.060
Great rack, by the way.

04:55.062 --> 04:56.295
Thank you.

04:56.297 --> 04:57.929
Well, thank Grandma
Griffin, really.

04:57.931 --> 05:00.632
It appears you have
a subcutaneous vestigial twin

05:00.634 --> 05:02.100
growing on your neck.

05:02.102 --> 05:03.302
What is that?

05:03.304 --> 05:04.803
Well, it's
an incomplete twin

05:04.805 --> 05:06.605
that never developed
into a fully-formed person

05:06.607 --> 05:09.074
but still exists as a growth
feeding off your body.

05:09.076 --> 05:10.074
Now, hold still.

05:10.076 --> 05:12.077
I'm just gonna give you
a little topical anesthetic,

05:12.079 --> 05:13.145
and we'll have
a closer look.

05:16.916 --> 05:17.983
(high-pitched voice):
Hi, everybody!

05:17.985 --> 05:19.918
Aah! What the
hell is that?!

05:19.920 --> 05:21.920
Oh, my God!
It's a little me!

05:21.922 --> 05:23.989
Well, it looks as if he's more
fully formed than we thought.

05:23.991 --> 05:26.625
Wow, your wife
is gorgeous!

05:26.627 --> 05:28.093
Is that a foot?

05:28.095 --> 05:29.261
Almost!

05:29.263 --> 05:30.595
This is awesome!

05:30.597 --> 05:32.164
Finally, I'll have an
interesting silhouette

05:32.166 --> 05:34.666
for the beginning of
my spoken-word jazz.

05:34.668 --> 05:37.302
(stand-up bass plays
slow jazz)

05:37.304 --> 05:39.304
I left...

05:39.306 --> 05:41.306
my poem...

05:41.308 --> 05:43.375
at home.

05:49.115 --> 05:51.950
MALE ANNOUNCER (over TV):
We now return to <i>Quantum Creep.</i>

05:51.952 --> 05:54.019
♪

05:55.955 --> 05:57.956
Al, what year is it?

05:57.958 --> 05:59.858
1972.
Cool.

05:59.860 --> 06:02.527
I'm gonna go show my penis
to some kids.

06:02.529 --> 06:04.996
Hey, Dad. How'd it
go at the hospital?

06:04.998 --> 06:07.032
Kids, remember
how when you were little,

06:07.034 --> 06:08.500
you always wanted
a neck uncle?

06:08.502 --> 06:10.302
No.
Well, now
you got one!

06:10.304 --> 06:11.636
(screaming)

06:11.638 --> 06:12.971
What is that thing?!

06:12.973 --> 06:14.673
This is my vestigial twin.

06:14.675 --> 06:15.974
I named him Chip.

06:15.976 --> 06:17.642
You know, like
"chip off the old neck."

06:17.644 --> 06:19.811
I like to poke him
'cause it makes him happy,

06:19.813 --> 06:21.980
and I feel it a little bit
in my nads.

06:21.982 --> 06:24.516
(both giggle)

06:24.518 --> 06:26.051
Well, keep that freakish thing
under wraps.

06:26.053 --> 06:28.019
I don't want it
cramping my style

06:28.021 --> 06:29.421
while I'm macking on toddlers.

06:34.060 --> 06:36.061
See you around, bitch.

06:36.063 --> 06:38.330
You know, Lois, a lot of times
you go into someone's house,

06:38.332 --> 06:40.232
and it's just a house,
but you can tell

06:40.234 --> 06:42.868
this is a home
by all the love here.

06:42.870 --> 06:44.169
Aw!
Aw!
Aw!
Aw!

06:44.171 --> 06:47.038
Peter, this seems unnatural,
and, quite frankly, dangerous.

06:47.040 --> 06:49.508
Hey, you must be the owner
of that Prius outside.

06:49.510 --> 06:51.009
Thanks for saving
the world.

06:51.011 --> 06:52.210
He gets it.

06:52.212 --> 06:55.013
He gets what we Prius
owners are trying to do.

06:55.015 --> 06:57.048
Wow, the world
is such a cool place.

06:57.050 --> 06:59.050
There's so much
I want to do and see!

06:59.052 --> 07:01.586
Oh, he's such a great
energy to have around.

07:01.588 --> 07:04.689
Ah, Chip, I am gonna show you
all kinds of cool stuff.

07:04.691 --> 07:08.026
My Hot Wheels, my lawn darts,
even my new musket.

07:08.028 --> 07:10.061
(rapid, rhythmic whirring)

07:10.063 --> 07:11.930
Peter, what the
hell are you doing?

07:11.932 --> 07:14.065
Lois, I thought
I heard a noise downstairs.

07:14.067 --> 07:15.567
Go stall 'em for 20 minutes

07:15.569 --> 07:17.702
and pray that it's not
too damp in here.

07:17.704 --> 07:19.704
(strums chord)

07:19.706 --> 07:21.406
Man, how do you know
so many songs?

07:21.408 --> 07:23.375
Oh, when you're trapped
under a layer of fat,

07:23.377 --> 07:25.877
a muffled folk song
is like manna from Heaven.

07:25.879 --> 07:26.912
Give me a C.

07:26.914 --> 07:28.713
(strums chord)

07:28.715 --> 07:31.716
♪ Michael, row
the boat ashore ♪

07:31.718 --> 07:34.920
♪ Hallelujah

07:34.922 --> 07:38.123
BOTH:
♪ Michael, row the boat ashore

07:38.125 --> 07:41.059
♪ Hallelujah

07:41.061 --> 07:43.261
Sister, help
to trim the sail.

07:43.263 --> 07:46.465
♪ Sister, help
to trim the sail ♪

07:46.467 --> 07:49.468
♪ Hallelujah

07:49.470 --> 07:51.903
♪ Sister, help to trim...

07:51.905 --> 07:52.904
(roaring)

07:52.906 --> 07:54.272
Aah! Run!

07:54.274 --> 07:57.843
No, Peter, gently stroke
his snout counterclockwise.

08:01.080 --> 08:02.781
Wow, it's working.

08:02.783 --> 08:05.150
There's a universal language
for all creatures,

08:05.152 --> 08:06.751
and it's called love.

08:06.753 --> 08:08.453
Now, how about
that River Jordan?

08:08.455 --> 08:12.090
♪ River Jordan
is deep and wide ♪

08:12.092 --> 08:14.993
♪ Hallelujah

08:14.995 --> 08:16.261
Join us, bear!

08:16.263 --> 08:19.331
ALL:
♪ Milk and honey
on the other side ♪

08:19.333 --> 08:22.934
♪ Hallelujah.

08:22.936 --> 08:24.703
(strums ending chord)

08:27.139 --> 08:28.940
Good morning, boys.

08:28.942 --> 08:30.775
What's in store
for today?

08:30.777 --> 08:32.944
Well, I thought we'd start
with a vigorous power walk

08:32.946 --> 08:34.479
around the neighborhood.

08:34.481 --> 08:37.282
Whoa, whoa, whoa. I was thinking
we would just watch <i>Dr. Oz</i>

08:37.284 --> 08:39.084
and eat cold cuts
off our stomach.

08:41.954 --> 08:44.523
Those people ain't taking
good care of themselves.

08:44.525 --> 08:46.825
What?! But there's so much
to do and experience!

08:46.827 --> 08:47.959
Did you know

08:47.961 --> 08:49.961
that the Quahog Museum
has an interactive display

08:49.963 --> 08:51.830
on the history
of the garment district?

08:51.832 --> 08:53.465
Oh, look, Chip, Chip,
slow down, all right?

08:53.467 --> 08:55.033
You know, just because
everything's new to you

08:55.035 --> 08:57.002
doesn't mean
you have to do it all at once.

08:57.004 --> 08:59.037
Peter, where's your sense
of fun and adventure?

08:59.039 --> 09:01.373
You're starting to sound
like a stick-in-the-mud.

09:01.375 --> 09:03.008
Well, that stuff
sounds exhausting.

09:03.010 --> 09:05.477
I'm just being honest,
like George Washington.

09:05.479 --> 09:08.046
George, did you chop down
our cherry tree?

09:08.048 --> 09:10.181
I cannot tell
a lie. Yes.

09:10.183 --> 09:12.851
And what is this pamphlet
I found under your bed

09:12.853 --> 09:14.686
called "The Boston He Party?"

09:14.688 --> 09:16.421
Not mine.

09:21.160 --> 09:23.328
Wow! Is there any
better time in the world

09:23.330 --> 09:25.497
than 11:00 a.m.
on a Wednesday?

09:25.499 --> 09:28.333
You already have two days
of hard work under your belt,

09:28.335 --> 09:30.335
and there's so much
more work to come.

09:30.337 --> 09:32.504
Look, I'm trying to get
this stuff done here.

09:32.506 --> 09:34.739
Griffin, did you finish
those purchasing reports?

09:34.741 --> 09:36.341
Oh, that voice!

09:36.343 --> 09:37.876
It's like God sneezing!

09:37.878 --> 09:39.177
What the hell is this?

09:39.179 --> 09:41.012
They found a guy
on my neck.

09:41.014 --> 09:42.012
Hello there.

09:42.014 --> 09:44.749
I've never met a supervisor,
slash supermodel before.

09:44.751 --> 09:46.351
Do you like crab?

09:46.353 --> 09:49.020
There's a knockout crab place
right around the corner.

09:49.022 --> 09:50.221
What the hell are you doing?

09:50.223 --> 09:52.223
I'm using my knowledge
of the local food scene

09:52.225 --> 09:54.459
to get this woman
to go to bed with me.

09:55.428 --> 09:57.696
Well, now we know.

09:57.698 --> 10:00.098
I can taste
what he eats.

10:02.068 --> 10:04.235
What are we watching?
Oh, it's just a tennis match.

10:04.237 --> 10:06.037
So this is tennis!

10:06.039 --> 10:07.372
(racket hits ball)
Wow!

10:07.374 --> 10:12.277
(to tennis balls hitting):
Wow! Wow! Wow! Wow! Wow!

10:12.279 --> 10:13.712
MAN (on TV):
15-love.

10:13.714 --> 10:14.946
That was just one point?!

10:14.948 --> 10:17.916
Federer and Hastings are known
for their long rallies.

10:17.918 --> 10:19.050
Federer to serve.

10:19.052 --> 10:23.888
Wow! Wow! Wow!
Wow! Wow!

10:23.890 --> 10:25.957
Wow! Wow!

10:25.959 --> 10:29.894
Wow! Wow! Wow! Wow!

10:29.896 --> 10:31.396
Wow!

10:31.398 --> 10:32.597
15 all.

10:32.599 --> 10:33.898
And this is just
the first game

10:33.900 --> 10:36.067
of the first round
of a three-week tournament?

10:36.069 --> 10:37.435
Yay!

10:37.437 --> 10:39.070
(sighs)
This is more painful
than sitting

10:39.072 --> 10:41.406
through those
parent-teacher-cheetah meetings.

10:41.408 --> 10:43.742
So, in short, your kids
are all doing great.

10:43.744 --> 10:45.110
Keep reading to
them every night,

10:45.112 --> 10:47.412
and I think we're gonna
have a great year.

10:47.414 --> 10:48.947
So unless there
are any questions,

10:48.949 --> 10:50.081
thank you all
for coming.

10:50.083 --> 10:52.250
Uh, yeah, I noticed
the hot lunch menu

10:52.252 --> 10:54.085
doesn't feature
any gazelle.

10:54.087 --> 10:55.286
(others groan loudly)

10:55.288 --> 10:57.122
I'll bring that
up to the board.

10:57.124 --> 10:59.457
Yeah. See, I-I heard
that last year,

10:59.459 --> 11:02.494
(chuckling): and...
here we are again.

11:02.496 --> 11:05.930
♪

11:05.932 --> 11:07.499
Listen, Doc, is
there any way

11:07.501 --> 11:09.434
you can have this thing
on my neck removed?

11:09.436 --> 11:11.803
Well, Mr. Griffin, your organs
and his are intertwined.

11:11.805 --> 11:13.304
That would be a highly
dangerous procedure.

11:13.306 --> 11:14.673
You could die.

11:14.675 --> 11:16.441
On the other hand,
if you live,

11:16.443 --> 11:18.276
I'll let you pick any prize
off that shelf.

11:18.278 --> 11:19.978
Even the tiny
pinball machine?

11:19.980 --> 11:21.680
Oh, that-that shouldn't
have been up there.

11:21.682 --> 11:23.782
Look, Doc, you got to do
the procedure, all right?

11:23.784 --> 11:25.116
I-I don't care
if I die.

11:25.118 --> 11:26.818
I mean, maybe in
my next life,

11:26.820 --> 11:28.753
I'll come back as an
air bag or something.

11:30.956 --> 11:33.625
(rhythmic ticking)

11:33.627 --> 11:36.027
It's okay. It's okay.
Peter's got you.

11:36.029 --> 11:37.162
Don't you worry.

11:37.164 --> 11:38.963
Everything's gonna
be all right.

11:38.965 --> 11:42.133
Is my wife okay?
No, the ski boots
that was in the back

11:42.135 --> 11:44.169
flew up and chopped
her head off.

11:44.171 --> 11:47.539
You can turn your blinker
off now; it's very annoying.

11:50.309 --> 11:53.211
♪

12:02.655 --> 12:04.489
Nurse, have somebody
fix that clock.

12:04.491 --> 12:05.690
It's very distracting.

12:05.692 --> 12:07.859
All right,
let's get this started.

12:07.861 --> 12:10.829
♪

12:10.831 --> 12:12.897
(machine beeping)

12:14.667 --> 12:16.568
All right, halfway done.

12:16.570 --> 12:18.236
Time for a break.

12:23.042 --> 12:25.076
♪ I hate myself

12:25.078 --> 12:27.212
♪ For loving you

12:27.214 --> 12:28.913
