12:28.915 --> 12:31.416
♪ From the things
that you do... ♪

12:35.588 --> 12:37.756
Oh, God, I'm
so nervous.

12:37.758 --> 12:40.091
Thank God Stewie's too
little to understand.

12:40.093 --> 12:42.594
Look at him over there,
playing that board game.

12:42.596 --> 12:44.095
Ah, three.

12:44.097 --> 12:46.197
Okay, one, two...

12:46.199 --> 12:48.032
Sorry!

12:48.034 --> 12:51.269
ANNOUNCER:
<i>Sorry! The board game</i>
<i>that teaches you to be a dick.</i>

12:52.538 --> 12:55.039
Dr. Hartman, is everything
all right with my dad?

12:55.041 --> 12:57.375
Griffins, I'm
afraid we lost him.

12:57.377 --> 12:59.377
What?!
Oh, my God!

12:59.379 --> 13:01.212
Hey, guys.
Oh, there he is.

13:01.214 --> 13:03.214
It worked!
I'm free at last!

13:03.216 --> 13:05.283
But what about Chip?
Where's Chip?

13:05.285 --> 13:08.453
Hey, everybody,
look who's walking!

13:08.455 --> 13:10.255
OTHERS:
Chip!

13:10.257 --> 13:12.891
Oh, Chip,
I'm so glad you're okay.

13:12.893 --> 13:14.726
Yeah, and I'm
okay, too.

13:14.728 --> 13:17.095
So, uh, you know, Chip,
now that you're a free man,

13:17.097 --> 13:18.930
this is a chance
for you to go out

13:18.932 --> 13:20.465
and make a real life
for yourself someplace.

13:20.467 --> 13:21.633
I'll tell you what,

13:21.635 --> 13:23.234
anywhere you want to
go, I'll FedEx you.

13:23.236 --> 13:25.069
What are you
talking about, Peter?

13:25.071 --> 13:27.071
Chip is part of our family.

13:27.073 --> 13:28.907
He's staying with us.
What?!

13:28.909 --> 13:30.909
Yay!
Yay!
Awesome!

13:30.911 --> 13:32.977
Hey, hey, Dad?
Yeah, I'm done.

13:32.979 --> 13:34.813
Can you pick me up?

13:34.815 --> 13:36.881
Oh, that's okay;
I have a book.

13:43.622 --> 13:45.089
Oh, hey, Peter.

13:45.091 --> 13:46.457
Lois, where's the couch?

13:46.459 --> 13:49.093
Chip redecorated the room
to improve the feng shui.

13:49.095 --> 13:52.096
He said our old furniture was
blocking the flow of energy.

13:52.098 --> 13:54.599
I had my life's
fart savings in that couch!

13:54.601 --> 13:57.101
And where are the drapes?
Chip took them

13:57.103 --> 13:59.470
to make play clothes
for the children.
What?!

13:59.472 --> 14:01.339
(Chip and others laughing)

14:01.341 --> 14:03.074
(laughter continues)

14:04.677 --> 14:06.277
Oh, hey, Peter.
You're home.

14:06.279 --> 14:08.112
Hi, Dad!
Hi, Daddy.

14:08.114 --> 14:09.647
We dug a lake
for this!

14:09.649 --> 14:11.082
ALL:
Whoa!

14:12.117 --> 14:14.118
Come out of that water at once!

14:14.120 --> 14:15.620
Gosh, isn't Chip
wonderful?

14:15.622 --> 14:17.188
No, he's not wonderful,
Lois; he's annoying.

14:17.190 --> 14:20.024
I don't get why everyone's
so in love with that guy.

14:20.026 --> 14:22.193
What's so great about him?
Well, to be honest,

14:22.195 --> 14:25.463
the same thing that used to be
so great about you.

14:25.465 --> 14:27.131
What? What are you
talking about?

14:27.133 --> 14:28.466
Just that when
you were younger,

14:28.468 --> 14:31.202
you were as passionate
and full of life as him.

14:33.038 --> 14:34.138
(high-pitched):
Hey, boys,

14:34.140 --> 14:36.407
catch me
if you can!

14:38.477 --> 14:40.645
Oh, crap!
I didn't realize they had bikes!

14:40.647 --> 14:42.981
(groans)
What are they gonna do
when they catch me?

14:42.983 --> 14:44.983
Oh, boy, I got a
back-of-the-head punch coming,

14:44.985 --> 14:46.351
I just know it!

14:46.353 --> 14:49.721
♪

14:52.057 --> 14:55.059
LOIS:
♪ It seems today
that all you see ♪

14:55.061 --> 14:57.528
What the hell?
♪ Is violence in movies

14:57.530 --> 14:59.364
♪ And sex on TV

14:59.366 --> 15:03.067
♪ But where are those
good old-fashioned values ♪

15:03.069 --> 15:05.169
♪ On which we used to rely?

15:05.171 --> 15:07.405
What the...? What the
hell is going on here?

15:07.407 --> 15:09.173
You're singing our
song without me?

15:09.175 --> 15:11.075
Oh, sorry, Peter,
we couldn't find you.

15:11.077 --> 15:13.177
Do you want to sing
your part, Peter?

15:13.179 --> 15:14.846
Go ahead.

15:14.848 --> 15:17.081
♪ But where are
the fashioned ♪

15:17.083 --> 15:18.683
♪ Good fashion...

15:18.685 --> 15:21.252
I don't want to!
(sobbing)

15:21.254 --> 15:25.023
♪

15:25.025 --> 15:26.691
I tell you,
Chip is making my life

15:26.693 --> 15:28.092
a living hell,
you guys.

15:28.094 --> 15:30.194
Remind me again, Chip is
that African kid you adopted?

15:30.196 --> 15:32.530
No, that was Chocolate Chip.
We gave him back to Kenya.

15:32.532 --> 15:35.066
But I can't take it anymore.
I got to get rid of him.

15:35.068 --> 15:37.068
Well, what are
you gonna do?
I don't know yet,

15:37.070 --> 15:38.369
but I'll come up
with something.

15:38.371 --> 15:39.938
After all, I'm the guy
who invented

15:39.940 --> 15:42.240
"Choose Your Own Adventure
or Have Pie in Bed."

15:42.242 --> 15:44.375
I picked the pie again.

15:44.377 --> 15:46.444
♪

15:49.882 --> 15:53.384
Hey, welcome back to
the    <i>Mikey Tony Magnanimous H,</i>

15:53.386 --> 15:55.887
where real people get
magnanimous about real things.

15:55.889 --> 15:58.423
This week's real thing--
hey, Native Americans,

15:58.425 --> 16:00.425
if I saw you
on the street begging,

16:00.427 --> 16:02.393
I'd throw a buck
in your moccasin.

16:02.395 --> 16:04.095
Next week's magnanimous thing--

16:04.097 --> 16:07.098
I'm wearing this yellow
bracelet. You're welcome.

16:07.100 --> 16:09.267
(growling)
Peter, what the
hell is that thing?

16:09.269 --> 16:11.269
It's a dingo.
I named him Bingo.

16:11.271 --> 16:13.438
If you can't have fun
with that, you're crazy.

16:13.440 --> 16:14.505
(growling)

16:15.474 --> 16:16.641
Hey, Peter.

16:16.643 --> 16:18.076
Wh-What's that?

16:18.078 --> 16:20.611
Oh, he's gonna turn you
into a pile on Joe's lawn.

16:20.613 --> 16:22.647
What?!
Here, let's play
steak catch.

16:22.649 --> 16:23.948
Oh, boy, I got it!

16:23.950 --> 16:25.116
Hey, back to you, Peter!

16:25.118 --> 16:26.985
Ah, cool! Steak catch!

16:26.987 --> 16:29.253
I'm gonna use my one
steak-in-the-pants time-out.

16:29.255 --> 16:31.756
(growling)
Aah! No!
Not me! Not me!

16:31.758 --> 16:33.091
Attack him! Aah!

16:33.093 --> 16:36.694
Hey, um, it's 3:00 p.m.
Should I give up on breakfast?

16:37.663 --> 16:38.830
Aah! Brian!

16:38.832 --> 16:40.131
Browser history--
clear it!

16:40.133 --> 16:43.935
Peter, that dingo was meant
to eat me, wasn't it?

16:43.937 --> 16:45.670
Why would you do that?

16:45.672 --> 16:48.006
Because my life was fine
before you showed up.

16:48.008 --> 16:50.608
My family liked me,
and-and I didn't feel bad

16:50.610 --> 16:52.276
about not ever doing new stuff.

16:52.278 --> 16:54.846
Well, I never asked to
grow out of your neck.

16:54.848 --> 16:57.949
My life was better
before I met you, too!

16:57.951 --> 17:00.785
You're a terrible brother,
husband and father.

17:00.787 --> 17:03.287
I'm out of here,
and you could go to hell!

17:03.289 --> 17:06.124
Wow, what a nice day out!
Look! A rainbow!

17:06.126 --> 17:07.792
I did it.

17:07.794 --> 17:09.027
He's gone.

17:09.029 --> 17:12.630
Just as easy as
the creation of techno music.

17:12.632 --> 17:14.632
Wait a minute,
what key are we in?

17:14.634 --> 17:16.634
No, no, no, no,
no, none of that.

17:16.636 --> 17:20.238
♪

17:21.306 --> 17:23.141
Oh, hey, Peter.
Where's Chip?

17:23.143 --> 17:25.043
I haven't seen him
all day.

17:25.045 --> 17:26.811
He likes to yell out
"Good luck!"

17:26.813 --> 17:28.513
after they read
each lottery number.

17:28.515 --> 17:30.048
He's gone.
I threw him out.

17:30.050 --> 17:31.349
You what?
No!

17:31.351 --> 17:33.151
Peter, how could you?

17:33.153 --> 17:35.219
Whoa, whoa, what are you all
coming down on me for?

17:35.221 --> 17:37.822
Meg throws away people who come
out of her body all the time,

17:37.824 --> 17:38.823
nobody says nothing.

17:38.825 --> 17:40.892
Peter, Chip was
a part of our family.

17:40.894 --> 17:42.160
And he's so little.

17:42.162 --> 17:44.028
He can get hurt
out there on his own.

17:44.030 --> 17:45.830
We got to go find him.

17:45.832 --> 17:47.999
We should look for him
in the ball pit at McDonald's.

17:48.001 --> 17:50.034
You can just leave me there;
I'll conduct the search.

17:50.036 --> 17:52.003
Meg's right!
Come on, kids,

17:52.005 --> 17:54.405
let's go find Chip
and bring him back!

17:54.407 --> 17:56.908
You guys do whatever you want.
I got stuff to do, anyway.

17:56.910 --> 17:58.910
I got to get ready
for my Bar Mitzvah.

17:58.912 --> 18:00.878
♪ Baruch atah Adonai

18:00.880 --> 18:03.548
♪ I want fancy things
like my friend Ephraim ♪

18:03.550 --> 18:05.083
♪ I want the newest
ten-speed bicycle ♪

18:05.085 --> 18:08.019
♪ That I will ride once, but
then I will call my parents ♪

18:08.021 --> 18:09.854
♪ And have them come get me

18:09.856 --> 18:13.024
♪ I want to swim in the pool
but only with my shirt on ♪

18:13.026 --> 18:15.093
♪ I want to lose
my virginity at 24 ♪

18:15.095 --> 18:16.694
♪ But tell everyone
I was 16... ♪

18:16.696 --> 18:19.931
♪

18:20.899 --> 18:23.634
Ah, crap, I'm out of beer.

18:24.937 --> 18:27.038
Great. I have to walk
down these stairs

18:27.040 --> 18:29.907
the one day I wore heels.

18:29.909 --> 18:30.942
(yelling)

18:30.944 --> 18:32.376
(screaming)

18:32.378 --> 18:33.911
(grunting in pain)

18:33.913 --> 18:35.079
Son of a bitch!

18:35.081 --> 18:36.881
I think I broke my leg!

18:36.883 --> 18:39.450
(grunting)

18:39.452 --> 18:42.220
There's no way I'm gonna make it
back up those stairs.

18:42.222 --> 18:43.654
(phone ringing)

18:45.057 --> 18:46.324
Nope.

18:48.060 --> 18:50.261
Peter? It's me, Chip.

18:50.263 --> 18:53.264
Listen, I... I'm sorry
for the mean things I said.

18:53.266 --> 18:55.533
Help!
Peter?

18:57.302 --> 18:59.637
Holy smokes!
Peter, are you okay?

18:59.639 --> 19:01.139
These books was already
down here!

19:01.141 --> 19:02.507
I'm not a nerd!

19:03.142 --> 19:04.609
Oh, my God!

19:04.611 --> 19:07.278
We got to get this leg set
and get you to the hospital!

19:07.280 --> 19:09.714
Oh, cool. That's the place
with all the <i>Ghostbusters</i> cars!

19:10.749 --> 19:12.016
(grunts)

19:19.458 --> 19:21.993
(grunting)

19:24.263 --> 19:26.531
(loud grunting)

19:28.000 --> 19:29.600
(high-pitched
flatulence)
(giggles)

19:29.602 --> 19:31.936
If you had only done that
while you were here,

19:31.938 --> 19:33.337
we wouldn't be in this mess.

19:36.975 --> 19:38.976
Mr. Griffin,
you're a lucky man.

19:38.978 --> 19:42.113
If it weren't for Chip here,
you might have lost your leg.

19:42.115 --> 19:43.781
The bad news is,
we did an X-ray,

19:43.783 --> 19:45.950
and your body is full
of a spooky skeleton man.

19:45.952 --> 19:48.853
Gosh, Chip, I don't
know how to thank you.

19:48.855 --> 19:50.154
No problem, Peter.

19:50.156 --> 19:52.123
You would have done
the same thing for me.

19:52.125 --> 19:54.959
You know, Chip, Lois
was right about you.

19:54.961 --> 19:56.627
You are special.

19:56.629 --> 19:59.664
You've got all the sense of
wonder that I somehow lost.

19:59.666 --> 20:01.966
I got so used to watching TV

20:01.968 --> 20:03.968
and looking for tiny
jean fibers in my nuts,

20:03.970 --> 20:06.871
I forgot there's a whole
world out there to experience.

20:06.873 --> 20:08.639
Thank you for
showing me that.

20:08.641 --> 20:10.308
As far as I'm concerned,

20:10.310 --> 20:12.543
you're a permanent
part of our family now.

20:12.545 --> 20:15.213
Well, that sure is nice of you,
Peter, but...

20:15.215 --> 20:17.648
there's a big old world
out there.

20:17.650 --> 20:20.151
I want to go out
and experience it for myself.

20:20.153 --> 20:21.986
ALL:
Aw!
Why?

20:21.988 --> 20:25.323
Well, I'm sorry to see you go,
but I understand.

20:25.325 --> 20:27.625
Oh, we're gonna miss you, Chip.

20:30.996 --> 20:35.066
I'm too tough to cry,
but I'm gonna miss you, too.

20:38.570 --> 20:41.005
Safe travels, buddy,
and keep in touch.

20:41.007 --> 20:42.173
I will!

20:42.175 --> 20:44.709
Whee!

20:44.711 --> 20:46.377
Good-bye, Chip!
Bye!

20:46.379 --> 20:48.579
Come back soon, okay?

20:48.581 --> 20:50.414
PATRICK STEWART:
<i>But Chip never did come back.</i>

20:50.416 --> 20:56.854
<i>He became the new, young,</i>
<i>funny kid on ABC's</i> The Middle.

20:56.856 --> 20:58.522
Captioned by
Media Access Group at WGBH
access.wgbh.org

20:58.524 --> 21:00.591
Wow! This is just a whole
bunch of loud garbage!
